text: Charlestown Sarsfields GAA () is a Gaelic Athletic Association club in Charlestown, County Mayo, Ireland. Their most notable achievement was winning the Connacht Senior Club Football Championship in 2001. Tom Parsons is a notable current player, having won two Connacht titles with Mayo. ==Name== It's known as Fr.
